added.title: Excalibear
added.description: On the Bears' visit to a medieval vegetable-village, Grizz starts to believe that he's the rightful king.

added.title: Meat House
added.description: The Bears and their new friend Squatter Otter attempt to live in mysterious house made of meat.

added.title: Pirate Parrot Polly
added.description: On their quest for hidden treasure, the Bears team up with Polly the Parrot Pirate.

added.title: Baby Bear Genius
added.description: Ice Bear receives an invitation to attend a prestigious school for baby geniuses… but Grizz and Panda do not.

added.title: Bug City Sleuths
added.description: To survive in a city inhabited by bugs, the Bears become noir-style detectives.

added.title: Total Trauma Rama
added.description: Duncan, normally the bad kid, has an identity crisis when his pranks start curing people of their fears.

added.title: The Doomed Ballooned Marooned
added.description: After over-decorating a birthday table with balloons several kids float away to a deserted island.

added.title: Legends of the Paul
added.description: Duncan grows jealous of Paul's 100 year time out and determined to be King of the Pranks, has to team up with Paul, learn his ways, then double-cross and become a legend.

added.title: A Bridgette Too Far
added.description: As season three draws to a close, Bridgette becomes desperate to star in an episode.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: This One Goes to 11
added.description: During one last stop by a toy store before Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max's maiden voyage across the Atlantic, Ben runs into an old bully, Kevin 11, who now has new powers. He's able to transform into aliens just like Ben, such as the bootleg doppelganger of Cannonbolt. Wreckingbolt!

added.title: Rath of Con
added.description: Back stateside, Ben can't get into a cat cosplay competition, Top Tail, without a costume of his own; but when he goes Rath, a new cat-like alien with an attitude, Ben's newfound wild side quickly becomes much more than he bargained for.

added.title: Poles Apart
added.description: A trip to the South Pole goes upside down when Team Tennyson lands on the North Pole instead, but Ben quickly discovers the culprits: Solar & Polar Twain, magnetically-powered scientists who want to hold the world ransom by threatening to reverse Earth's magnetic poles!

added.title: Show Don't Tell
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max arrive at a Native American national park to witness the Ayasha Plinths, an ancient Stonehenge-like rock formation. But when the sinister sorcerer Hex arrives, Ben must battle against a beast Hex magically made out of huge rocks!

added.title: Welcome to Zombozo-Zone!
added.description: During medieval times, Team Tennyson must fight to remember that they're not in the past at all, but actually at a Renaissance-esque faire, where "King Zombozo" has hypnotized its guests into thinking they live in the past!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 2
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 3
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Perfect Day
added.description: Ben thinks he's having 'the perfect day' only to realize he's been put in a dream world by Enoch and the Forever Knights who are after the Omnitrix. Ben's "dream world" soon becomes a nightmare world, with Ben forced to live out his ultimate terror...being stuck at school! But with Max and Gwen's help, he's able to vanquish his nightmare foes and re-enter the real world where he takes down  Enoch...only to reveal an even more powerful knight...The Forever King.

added.title: Divided We Stand
added.description: While at the beach, Ben discovers a new hero, Ditto, and soon has the ability to create multiple Dittos at once. These multiple Dittos can't agree on anything and drive Gwen crazy. However when the chips are down, these Dittos come together as one fighting force in order to defeat Animo and his army of replicant Stinkflies.

added.title: Don't Drink the Water
added.description: In Florida, Ben and Max accidentally come in contact with water from The Fountain of Youth. As a result, Max transforms into a kid and Ben a toddler, with Gwen having to deal with both of them. Our trio then must track down Hex who's found the source of the fountain and prevent him from drinking the water that will make him immortal and unstoppable.

added.title: Showdown Part I
added.description: The Faction infiltrates Galvan in an attempt to destroy Azmuth.  (Introducing new Nemetrix aliens Omnivoracious & Vicetopus.)

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Tummy Trouble
added.description: When the Incursean armada kidnaps the Gourmand Queen, Ben and Rook must get the warring Gormand factions to work together to save her and stop the Incursean invasion.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: While You Were Away
added.description: Dr. Psychobos and Princess Attea have invaded Rook's home planet Revonnah with an army of Incurseans! (Introducing new Ben alien, Astrodactyl.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 1
added.description: The Incursean Armada, with the help of Dr. Psychobos, have invaded the Earth. (Reintroducing old Ben alien, BenMummy.)

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
added.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Rad
added.description: With Plumber agents trapped in Incursean territory, Ben and Rook must employ the services of Rad Dudesman, the roughest, toughest smuggler in the galaxy.  (Introducing Rad Dudesman, return of classic Ben alien, Eye Guy.)

added.title: Evil's Encore
added.description: Dr. Animo reminisces about when he once took control of the Plumber's HQ in Mount Rushmore. (Flashback episode.)

added.title: Trial By Mino
added.description: Separated from the others, Kai and Zane discover a party of Geckles who suspect them of being in league with the Skull Sorcerer, and bring them before their leader, Chancellor Gulch, who subjects them to a "Trial-By-Mino."

added.title: The Skull Sorcerer
added.description: Separated from the others, Cole must trust his instincts and make the right choices to find his way to the surface to alert King Vangelis of the dangerous Skull Sorcerer.

added.title: The Real Fall!
added.description: An entire episode chronicles the ninja's most bizarre adventure yet: in which Cole, Princess Vania and Master Wu fall down a seemingly endless tunnel, into the bowels of Shintaro Mountain.

added.title: Dungeon Party
added.description: Having survived their fall into the mountain, Cole, Wu and Princess Vania befriend a motley group of survivors, called the Lowly, and are told the story of how they too ended up at "Rock-Bottom."

added.title: Dungeon Crawl!
added.description: Having joined forces with the Lowly in their quest to defeat King Vangelis, Cole, Wu, and Vania have to find a way out of the bottom of the mountain, a place said to be inescapable.

added.title: The Lady and the Queen/The AB's Silver Screen Debut
added.description: The Lady and the Queen: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be./The AB's Silver Screen Debut: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

added.title: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!/Magnus
added.description: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing./Magnus: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League/The Ancient Elder
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!/The Ancient Elder: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

added.title: Bakugan Wynton/The Boy from Brazil
added.description: Bakugan Wynton: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure./The Boy from Brazil: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

added.title: Haunted House/Two of a Kind
added.description: Haunted House: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!/Two of a Kind: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Toyman takes over the Justice League and turns them into avatars in a diabolical video game.

added.title: Repulse!
added.description: Luthor infects Superman with a magnetic charge that repels everything. As the repulsing charge grows, the Magnetized Man of Steel is fated to spend the rest of his life isolated in space unless the Justice League can figure out a way to free him.

added.title: Trick or Threat
added.description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

added.title: Speed Demon
added.description: Batman has to enlist the help of Jason Blood, aka the Demon, when Brother Blood turns the Batmobile into a sentient, demonic entity.

added.title: Hat Trick
added.description: When Felix Faust steals Zatanna's magical top hat, the Justice League must help retrieve it before the evil wizard can use it to create a magic portal, releasing the demon Ghast.

added.title: Convencion de Rath
added.description: De regreso en casa, Ben no puede inscribirse en un concurso de cosplay de gatos sin su propio disfraz. Pero cuando se convierte en Rath, un nuevo alienígena con aspecto felino y mal carácter, el lado salvaje que Ben acaba de descubrir pronto tendrá resultados inesperados.

added.title: Polos Opuestos
added.description: Un viaje al Polo Sur queda patas arriba cuando el equipo Tennyson aterriza en el Polo Norte. Pero Ben rápidamente descubre a los culpables: iSolar y Polar Twain, unos científicos con poder magnético que quieren chantajear al mundo amenazando con invertir los polos magnéticos de la Tierra!

added.title: No lo digas y Hazlo
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el Abuelo Max llegan a un parque nacional nativo americano para conocer los plintos de Ayasha, una antigua formación rocosa parecida a la de Stonehenge. Pero cuando llega el siniestro hechicero Hex, iBen debe luchar contra una bestia que Hex hizo mágicamente con rocas enormes!

added.title: Bienvenido a la Zona Zombozo
added.description: Durante tiempos medievales, el equipo Tennyson debe esforzarse por recordar que no están en el pasado, sino en una feria renacentista, idonde el "Rey Zombozo" ha hipnotizado a sus invitados para que crean que viven en el pasado!

added.title: Bloqueo de Tránsito
added.description: Cuando un paso elevado colapsa sobre la autopista, el equipo Tennyson queda varado en un embotellamiento junto con Simon Sez y familia. Pero cuando Ben y Simon se alían para enfrentar juntos al atasco, Simon solo consigue que las cosas sean mucho, pero mucho peores.

added.title: Juicio de Mino
added.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

added.title: El Hechicero Calavera
added.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: La Gran Caida
added.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

added.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
added.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

added.title: El Camino en el Calabozo
added.description: En su misión de derrotar al Rey Vangelis, Cole, Wu y Vania unen fuerzas con "Los de abajo" para encontrar una forma de salir del fondo de la montaña.

added.title: Ventila-hala
added.description: Chef le confisca la mega-bola a Owen y la guarda en su oficina. Duncan, viendo una oportunidad para conseguir ayuda escapando de la guardaería, lidera un equipo de fuga por los conductos del aire acondicionado para recuperarla.

added.title: Rules of the Game
added.description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Quiet Delivery
added.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Kana Goes Slow
added.description: When Kana's power goes out during a delivery run, Thomas teaches her that sometimes it's okay to go slow.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Bats
added.description: Can you see in the dark? Blippi can't either! But on this adventure Blippi and FETCH fly around in the dark with Matt the Bat who shows them how he uses echolocation to see and hear in the dark! Who needs eyes when you can use echo-echo-echoes?

added.title: Crane
added.description: It's the first day on the job for Kareem the Crane, and he's feeling very nervous. Luckily, Blippi and FETCH are there to lend a helping hand! Working together they help Kareem to do his work. Kareem gains confidence and Blippi learns how cranes help to build a skyscraper!

added.title: Flies
added.description: Lunch is ready! Prepared to eat his delicious sandwich, Blippi notices his old friend Horace the Fly. Horace is walking upside down on the ceiling, and after shrinking down, Blippi joins him. But how does Horace stick to the ceiling? A musical song and dance from Horace is the best way to find out!

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

added.title: Holiday Party
added.description: "Lighting up the farm for a big 'festive' celebration Lots of lights around the farm and decorations from different cultures"

added.title: Chinese New Year
added.description: The farm is decorated for Chinese New Year. A party is taking place!

added.title: Puddle Olympics
added.description: The kids take turns jumping over a puddle but Sylvester is afraid of the water.

added.title: A Lot Like Lola
added.description: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her.

added.title: Mother's Day Madness
added.description: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

added.title: Takers Keepers
added.description: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want.

added.title: To Tell the Tooth
added.description: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.
